    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.27a.28-29_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">28</fw>
                
                <fw type="imprint">
                    <unclear>Publi</unclear>shers of &#8212;
                        <lb/>
                    <hi rend="caps">THE WAUNETA BREEZE
                        <lb/>
                    ------
                        <lb/>
                    STANLEY C. SMITH</hi>
                        <lb/>
                    Editor &amp; Publisher
                        <lb/>
                    
                    <hi rend="caps">THE WAUNETA PUBLISHING CO.
                        <lb/>
                    PHONE 89
                        <lb/>
                    WAUNETA, NEBRASKA</hi>
                    
                    <figure>
                        <figDesc>Map of Nebraska with an arrow pointing to Wauneta</figDesc>
                        <p><hi rend="caps">SOUTH DAKOTA
                        <unclear/>
                        IOWA
                        <unclear/>
                        COLORADO
                        <unclear/>
                        WAUNTETA</hi></p>
                    </figure>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>My visit to your home last Saturday was truly memorable. Seeing you again and spending a few hours in your home was something I have looked forward to for many years. Your hospitality during our visit was wonderful, and certainly appreciated.</p>
                
                <p>I am sending you the second section from <hi rend="caps">THE BREEZE</hi> for this week, carrying the story of our visit with you.</p>
                
                <p>You will note that I was clum<del><unclear>b</unclear></del>sy in reporting your eloquence in many places--and for this I apologize. I <del>c</del><add>f</add>aced the fact many years ago that I am not a writer. Yet despite the shortcomings I know would appear in the finished article, I had to tell just a little of your story and of your contributions to all of us. I certainly hope I had the factual reporting correct.</p>
                
                <p>Our trip to your home was the first occasion I have had to be in Missouri in four <del>h</del><add>y</add>ears. It is every bit as beautiful as I remembered--but I don't think I would return to make my home if given the opportunity. We are in plains country here--much of it flat, dry and windy. Not too many people either. But for some dumb reason I like it and will probably spend the rest of my years in the West.</p>
                
                <p>I think of you often and hope the time betweem<sic>between</sic> our first visit last Saturday and the next time we meet will not be too long.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Your friend,</salute>
                
                    <signed>Stan</signed>
                    <signed>Stanley C. Smith</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            
